    english: "When the bishop was buried,\nGod wished to have another,\nwho should increase Christendom\nand should convert the heathens...\n\nAfter Meinhard\u2019s death in 1196, his successor Bishop Berthold attempted to continue the mission but was killed in battle with the Livs in 1198. His death convinced the German church that peaceful conversion was impossible \u2014 only a formal crusade could secure Christianity in the Baltic. Pope Innocent III issued a crusading bull, and Bishop Albert was appointed to lead the armed mission.",
